1. Quick Start Guide
Follow these steps to verify functionality in under 2 minutes:

Requirements: Ensure the Dynamic Storage and GameplayTags plugins are enabled in Edit > Plugins.

Set Data: In any Actor/Animation Blueprint, add a Set Dynamic Value node. Connect an "Integer" variable to the Value pin and enter MyTestKey in the Key field.

Get Data: Add a Get Dynamic Value node elsewhere in the graph. Enter MyTestKey in the Key field.

Confirm: Connect the Value output of the Get node to a Print String. The pin will automatically turn cyan. Compile and Play to see the stored value in your log.

2. Overview
The Dynamic Storage System is a high-performance C++ plugin that eliminates the need for repetitive casting and complex variable management in Blueprints. Using custom K2Nodes, it allows for seamless storage and retrieval of various data types through a unified "Wildcard" interface.

3. Key Features
Wildcard Property Support: "Get" and "Set" nodes automatically adapt to the connected data type.

Zero-Boilerplate Logic: Reduces the need for manual casting or large "Switch on Type" structures.

Modular Architecture: Features separate Runtime and UncookedOnly (Editor) modules for optimized packaging.

Native Integration: Designed to behave like native Unreal Engine nodes with context-sensitive pinning.

4. Installation
Navigate to fab and install it

5. Technical Specifications
Module Structure
DynamicStorage (Runtime): Handles core data containers and memory management.

DynamicStorageEditor (UncookedOnly): Contains K2Node logic and compiler instructions.

Supported Data Types
Primitives: Boolean, Byte, Integer, Int64, Float, Double.

Common Structs: Vector, Rotator, Transform.

Strings: FString, FName, FText.

Objects: UObject and Actor references.

Enums: Custom, Unreal built-in

6. Troubleshooting
Missing Nodes: Verify that the DynamicStorageEditor module is included in your .uplugin file.

